# Gabby’s Gazetteer

The who’s who and what’s what of the 6 seas.

![The Wended World 2022-05-30-14-01.jpeg](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**[[Atlas/Domovya/The Kingdom of Dennengard|The Kingdom of Dennengard]]**

They’ve got a new king kind of maybe? Doesn’t really matter he doesn’t do much. Their navy is a pain in the ass. You ever see a big fucking boat with no sense and blue flags? Then you’re in Dennian territory and you should just leave. Apparently they don’t like pirates.

(Constitutional Monarchy, with the Church heavily participating)

**The Vestov Commonwealth**

It exists. Kinda a shit place honestly though who would pass through more than once? Do they even have a dock? Sometimes folks talk about it all romantically, especially vets and sailors running from the last war, for some reason or another.

(Psuedo socialist farm towns, mostly just poor communes)

**Belavor Noble Corporations**

This state is run by Knights. Honestly it would be one of those things to avoid entirely if they didn’t own all the fucking banks. Trade is good and the Holy Warriors seem more concerned with their missions than policing the ports. As long as taxes are paid, money flows freely through the ports of Yusha, Novipristav, Hotrov, Anniden, Mozelk, and Zica. Zica is your last stop before Estarian territory. At least by sea. Their ports use Dennian laws.

(Literally a state ruled by a Knightly Order, the only of it’s kind)

**The Ostfelds**

Honestly you’ve never even been to these backwaters before this but it seems like small towns are the same everywhere as far as you know. Doesn’t seem to be very different from anywhere in Dennengard even if the locals seem patriotic.

(Formerly several monarchies, currently open and pastoral/farmland. The deeper politics you likely don’t know but if Luka’s Rest is an indication rule is contentious)

**The Estarian Empire**

The big deal hot shot empire in the east. They’ve been waging wars forever now, which means they seem to be everywhere. On ships, in trade, the Estarian coins are only going up in value and though they have some quaint ideas (God Kings and what not) their naval power is limited. They mostly hire, which is good for your business naturally.

(Absolute Monarchy, expanding Empire. Emperor chosen through might not hereditary at the moment)

**Volessia**

Volessia is honestly the most sensible place of them all. Everyone is out for themselves, and whoever is richest and carries the sharpest knife wins. The Queen in charge right now has to wrestle down every dick with more than ten men and 100gp pieces from calling himself a king.

(Psuedo Absolute monarch with underkings pulled from mercantile heavyweights)

**Yuria, Axos, Athosia and Depios**

These kingdoms kinda belong together. Honestly that might not even be the right names or borders anymore, they change with a frequency and their royal families are so inbred that sometimes they probably don’t know who’s in charge. Guilds and merchants thrive here though. These are the ships you wanna rob, cause Dennengard won’t care. One day Axios will pay you to knock over Depios and then Depios will turn around and ask you rob Axios. It’s a good time.

(A mix of monarchies, psuedo-republics, guild rules, with a lot of guilds and merchants helping buy their way into power mixed in, there’s more focus on city state powers here though and some towns are clearly republics, psuedodemocrachies, and more. Again, things change rapidly.)

**Sunnia (Nat 20 Perception)**

They call themselves an Empire but I mean, what have they done in the last hundred years? The people are cranky and the ports give folks a hard time. Still they export a ton of things still and you’re pretty sure if you put Sunnia before anything on the label people pay twice as much for it.

(Absolute Monarchy)

**Cytria**

An idyllic country. People are very fucking in love with the king currently in charge and they love to tell you about it. Have a sort of Ostfeldian vibe but less depressing and maybe more idiotic. They have a decent navy, decent land, and decent ports. The only thing you’ve heard notable is that the last king had to be toppled but for a country who toppled a monarch they seem incredibly happy.

(Monarchy)

**Dipaski, Tovstan, Kopetsia, Votia**

These are less countries, more states of the Estarian Empire. You only really noticed cause their coins all changed over. Their ships are still theirs, and the people still mingle dialects, but now they’ve started flying red flags and doing business by Estarian laws. Votia alone has probably the best boats of the bunch but they’re also the most distinct. You can always tell someone from Votia because unlike all the other crazies, they don’t spout that god-emperor crap.

**The Kingdom of Muria**

Muria has been at war with itself…forever? As far as you know anyways, you only pass trade along their way.

Nat 20: An extended civil war is good for your business but not neccesarily for the safety or stability of, oh you know, the people? the throne itself? Estara is right next door. Probably a matter of time.

**Belgrosia, Luria, Rechinia, Loslavia, Nedia, Osvina, Rosternia**

These countries share a lot of similarities culturally. Honestly you see one northern hinterland, you seen em all. Notable notes below:

-   Belgrosia: People here are a little more willing to look the other way than usual.
-   Rechinia: The tariffs here are high as fuck. Good for your business, bad for theirs.

(Unknown to you, likely a mix of things, with constitutional monarchies or oligarchies)

**Kolyvania**

The people here are strange. Kolyvania isn’t a country, it’s more of a region, and their only significant port is, at best, a pit stop for longer journeys. This is the sort of place people tell ghost stories about. If there’s a ruler or ruling body here you’ve never seen it. Nat 20: Despite being neighbors they’re happy to let pirates stop in their ports to avoid the Dennian ones.

(Unknown)

**Other Continents**

You’ve heard about continents further west and south but the supplies for those voyages are still expensive and mostly the province of the rich and royally backed. This has more to do with the vast _danger_ than the vast distance. The sea is still yet untamed.

Directly west is the Eostre, with their city states and their own sea trade, to the south you’ve heard it’s mostly unknown and uncharted. The waters there are far more dangerous.

**Perception 20 Addendums**

-   At sea all things being equal, you see a diversity of races, mainly human, elf, dwarf, and gnome, but goblins are a sizable employable group as well.
-   Far north you’ve occasionally caught sight of drow. Though this was maybe only once or twice.
-   Arstan has recently started using Estarian coins and taxes
-   Piracy reins heavily in Volessia and profits wildly in the southern nations. There’s a loose alliance of them somewhere nearby and rumors of an Island where pirates rein
